  "original_title": "\u0da2\u0db1\u0dcf\u0db0\u0dd2\u0db4\u0dad\u0dd2\u0db0\u0dd6\u0dbb\u0dba \u0dc4\u0dd2\u0dc3\u0dca\u0dc0\u0dd6 \u0d85\u0dc0\u0dc3\u0dca\u0dae\u0dcf\u0dc0\u0d9a \u0da2\u0db1\u0dcf\u0db0\u0dd2\u0db4\u0dad\u0dd2\u0dc0\u0dbb\u0dba\u0dcf \u0dad\u0ddd\u0dbb\u0dcf \u0db4\u0dad\u0dca \u0d9a\u0dbb\u0d9c\u0db1\u0dca\u0db1\u0dda \u0d9a\u0ddc\u0dc4\u0ddc\u0db8\u0daf?",
  "text_idx": {
    "en": {
      "title": "How can the president be elected when the presidency is vacant?",
      "author": "unknown",
      "body_lines": [
        "According to the Election of the President (Special Provisions) Act No. 2 of 1981, how to elect the President when the office of President becomes vacant, the Director of Communications of the Parliament H. e. Janakantha Silva made the announcement today.",
        "In the event that the office of the President becomes vacant in accordance with sub-article (1) of Article 38 of the Constitution, as specified in Article 40 of the Constitution, a person who is eligible to be elected to the office of President by the Parliament from among its members to hold the office only during the remaining period of the office of the President whose office is vacant. A member of Parliament should be elected as the President.",
        "This election is done in accordance with the provisions of the Election of the President (Special Provisions) Act No. 2 of 1981.",
        "In particular, this process is led by the General Secretary of the Parliament and the Speaker also has a vote in this poll. Also for this process the Parliament will meet for 3 days.",
        "Accordingly, the following steps will be taken to make this election under the provisions of the Act."
      ],
